            {# Explanations for the examples #}
            <div class="card p-2">
                <div class="card-header">
                    <h2>üîé How the examples are built</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body d-flex fd-column gap-1">
                    <div>
                        <h5 class="m-0">Card 1</h5>
                        <p class="mt-1">
                            The card uses a basic <code class="text-bold text-primary">.card</code> and adds <code
                                class="text-bold text-primary">.bg-primary</code> to the <code
                                class="text-bold text-primary">.card-header</code>.<br>
                            The <code class="text-bold text-primary">.card-footer</code> uses <code
                                class="text-bold text-primary">.bg-gray-300</code> to clearly separate it from the body.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h5 class="m-0">Card 2</h5>
                        <p class="mt-1">
                            The card adds <code class="text-bold text-primary">.border-primary</code> and <code
                                class="text-bold text-primary">.text-primary</code> to the <code
                                class="text-bold text-primary">.card</code>.<br>
                            This creates an outlined style with color coming from the border and text.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h5 class="m-0">Card 3</h5>
                        <p class="mt-1">
                            The card applies <code class="text-bold text-primary">.bg-warning</code> to the <code
                                class="text-bold text-primary">.card</code> for a bright warning look.<br>
                            It‚Äôs perfect for short notices or important messages.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h5 class="m-0">Card 4</h5>
                        <p class="mt-1">
                            The card uses <code class="text-bold text-primary">.border-danger</code> on the <code
                                class="text-bold text-primary">.card</code> to create a strong frame.<br>
                            The <code class="text-bold text-primary">.card-body</code> adds <code
                                class="text-bold text-primary">.border-y</code> and <code
                                class="text-bold text-primary">.border-danger</code> for a matching divider.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h5 class="m-0">Card 5</h5>
                        <p class="mt-1">
                            The card is built with a basic <code class="text-bold text-primary">.card</code> containing
                            a <code class="text-bold text-primary">.card-header</code>, <code
                                class="text-bold text-primary">.card-body</code>, and <code
                                class="text-bold text-primary">.card-footer</code>.<br>
                            No extra colors or borders ‚Äî just a clean structure to start from.
                        </p>
